Body: It is gattlib not gatlib. I was able to reproduce this error. ```ImportError: No module named 'gattlib'```
Not sure if it matters, but did you misspell gattlib in your code somewhere, or only in your stack overflow question?

pip install gattlib should work

For python3, use pip3

Make sure dependencies such as libbluetooth-dev,pkg-config,glib-2.0,lib-boost-python-dev,libboost-thread-dev are installed.

Required dependencies in gattlib module: Link
